description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 4 Registered Nursing Associate - General Outpatients&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE:&lt;/strong&gt; As well as working at the the main Royal Berkshire Hospital site in Reading, you will also be required at times to work at our other sites at Townlands in Henley and Bracknell Healthspace and Berkshire Independent Hospital - &lt;strong&gt;you must therefore be able to travel and be flexible.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking to recruit a highly motivated, enthusiastic Registered Nursing Associate. You will be working with our existing registered nurses and nursing care support workers in a variety of areas and services in this new role - it is an opportunity to extend your knowledge in all specialties and gain experience in an outpatient setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have excellent clinical, written and verbal communication skills and have completed the Trainee Nursing Associates course, gaining NMC registration&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will offer you a two year preceptorship and further development opportunities which as well as offering you the opportunity to consolidate your role could provide you with a structured career pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we offer a great team environment, learning and development opportunities and supervision support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to work in a hospital that values you, supports you in allowing you the time to really care and is committed to your professional development then please apply today!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sister Carmel Russell on 0118 322 7598 or carmel.russell@royalberkshire.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
